metadata.name: The Two Witnesses
metadata.description:
Both witnesses stand awestruck by the one who soars like a dove.

"You may call me 'the Ghost'; I have ruled over the heavenly places; I have carefully examined everything and looked into everything that is done on this planet. There isn't much to boast about, I'll tell you that much right now. Your lives are not as they should be due to lack of wisdom. I've witnessed everything, and all I see is smoke, mirrors, and humanity spitting into the wind."

4520 x 5978 px

Mixed Media on Aluminum

A Holographic Foil Piece by Holy Blood
